                                                <p> <hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE.—<name type="person">Private H. H. Bonham</name>, <name type="organization">Co. F,
                                                                7th Wisconsin Volunteers</name>, aged 17 years, was
                                                                wounded at <name type="BATTLE" key="259">the Wilderness, Virginia</name>, <date type="injury" when="1864-05-07">May 7th, 1864</date>, by a fragment of shell, which struck the
                                                  left breast near the sternum, two inches below the
                                                  clavicle. The cavity of the chest was not opened;
                                                  but there was lesion of its contents by contusion.
                                                  He was carried to the hospital of the 4th
                                                  division, Fifth Corps, and a simple bandage was
                                                  placed about the chest. On <date type="transfer" when="1864-05-11">May 11th</date>, he was
                                                                transferred to <name type="hospital">Harewood Hospital</name> at Washington;
                                                                on <date type="transfer" when="1864-05-15">the 15th</date>, to Cuyler Hospital, <name type="place">Germantown</name>,
                                                                whence he returned to duty on <date type="duty" when="1864-07-05">July 5th, 1864</date>.
                                                                Discharged from service on <date type="servicedischarge" when="1865-08-07">August 7th, 1865</date>.
                                                                <name type="person">Pension Examiner J. H. Hyde, M. D.</name>, reports, <date type="pension" when="1868-05-23">May
                                                                                23d, 1868</date>, that Bonham "suffers from palpitation
                                                  of the heart. He expectorates blood, and has
                                                  almost entirely lost the use of his left arm.
                                                  Disability three-fourths and permanent." </p>
                                                
